  <h2>Coppenbrügge</h2>
  <p>Coppenbrügge lies at the foot of the Ith ridge and together with Salzhemmendorf forms the <strong>Ith-Region</strong>. The town features a well-preserved medieval castle, idyllic villages and direct access to climbing areas.</p>
  <h3>Highlights</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Coppenbrügge Castle</strong> – Medieval castle with museum and events</li>
    <li><strong>Ith Ridge Path</strong> – Direct access to spectacular rock formations</li>
    <li><strong>Historic Town Centre</strong> – Half-timbered architecture</li>
  </ul>
  <h3>Getting Here</h3>
  <p>Coppenbrügge is conveniently located on the B1 road. Easily reachable from Hameln, Hildesheim and Hannover.</p>
</ContentLayout>
